metadata.name: Acid Drops #204
metadata.description:
Acid Drops is an algorithm that generates drops of LSD.  Each drop contains a colorful, silly, sometimes-scary little psychedelic world that is waiting to unfurl.  The drops are all spheres of exactly the same size, but each one dances around differently and refracts glimpses of a future psychedelic colorscape.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Elswhere Atlas #73
metadata.description:
Trying to navigate through a lucid dream, seeking serenity in chaos.

A generative art series created using noise, math, and p5js.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.06

metadata.name: Love #248
metadata.description:
We all experience love at different scales, ranging from scarcely perceived instances of kindness to unforgettable affections shown to us by family and friends, pets and partners. Each of these moments link us to the same boundless and enveloping interconnectedness that persists across space and time: the infinite source of our deepest aspirations.

Like the feeling of simple bliss, ‘Love’ portrays the visceral radiant light and warmth of our innermost joys. By taking a moment to open ourselves up, these swirling worlds of weightless and seemingly infinite brush strokes invite us to slow down and dwell in prismatic intuitive swells.

In doing so, we may find the immense and omnipresent love that needs only our awareness to be felt.

__________

Press 1-9 to load at different scales (1 = 2,000x2,000 (default), 9 = 10,000x10,000)
When zoomed in, once the output is fully loaded, you can click and drag to move around the canvas
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'B' to toggle the background texture on or off
Press 'A' to toggle the loading animation (recommended for very large scales)

Created with p5.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
__________
TENDER x teaboswell
May 2022

metadata.name: Paesaggio #162
metadata.description:
In this work I used the tools I learned in developing precedent works to generate a landscape with hills, flowers, streams, ruins, sky and clouds. The generated landscape gives the impression of a natural one but at the same time it has some "abstract" traits that reveal the geometrical properties of the noise generation process. This noise is used both for the morphological aspect and for colors assignment.

Developed with p5.js using WEBGL renderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.

[s] to save a 1600x1600 png.


Features:
"Palette": 12 colormap
"Sky":  Day, Night, Gray - 15% Gray, 20% Night, 65% Day
"Ruins": True, False - 33% True
"Streams": True, False - 33% True
"Flower": Red-Blue, Fuchsia-Yellow, Rose-Violet
"Border": True, False - 25% True


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.
